place.name: HUMBIE
place.gazetteerText: Humbie.-- par., SW. Haddingtonshire, 9316 ac., pop. 907; Humbie House, seat of Lord Polwarth, is 3½ miles NE. of Blackshiels; Humbie and Salton Wood stretches from Humbie church 2 miles N. into Salton par. (In 1887, John Bartholomew's Gazetteer of the British Isles)
